# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PVSnesLib build artifacts
#
# Everything below is generated from tracked source (C, hand-written .asm,
# PNG/BMP art, IT/WAV audio). `make clean` removes most of it; this list also
# keeps `git status` clean if a build aborts partway. Patterns have no leading
# slash, so they match in any subdirectory (slice1/, slice2/, …).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ROM output + Mesen debugger symbol file (and our portable-sed temp files)
*.sfc
*.sym
*.sym.tmp

# Linker scratch file
linkfile

# C → asm → obj intermediate stages (816-tcc / 816-opt / constify / wla-65816).
# NOTE: hand-written assembly sources use the .asm extension and ARE tracked
# (e.g. hdr.asm, data.asm). Only the generated .ps/.asp/.obj stages are ignored;
# make auto-deletes these on a successful build anyway.
*.ps
*.asp
*.obj

# Debug dumps — only produced when PVSNESLIB_DEBUG=1
*.dbg

# gfx4snes outputs (regenerated from the source .png/.bmp).
# In this toolchain, generated assembly *includes* use the .as / .inc extensions,
# while your hand-written assembly uses .asm — so ignoring these is safe.
*.pic
*.pal
*.map
*.pc7
*.mp7
*.til
*.m16
*.b16
*.o16
*.t16
*.as
*.inc

# smconv / snesbrr audio outputs (regenerated from .it / .wav).
# The generated soundbank has a .asm extension, so ignore it by name rather than
# globbing *.asm (which would wrongly catch hand-written assembly).
soundbank.asm
soundbank.h
soundbank.bnk
*.bnk
*.brr

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# macOS / editor noise
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
*.swp

# Mesen video / screen captures used for debugging (large, ephemeral)
*.avi
*.mp4

# Local clangd config — contains machine-specific absolute include paths.
# Lets the editor resolve <snes.h>; not used by the actual build (816-tcc).
compile_flags.txt
docs/*.md
gothicvania/preview